				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: PoP Ability: Ayonae's Tutalage<a name="6869"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 30 03 9:49 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>It DOES NOT increase you MOD, it increase you MOD CAP. There is a cap at 3.6 for a mod, regardless of what instrument/IM you have. AT raises the MOD CAP by .2 per rank.  You now have a HARD CAP on MODs of 4.2, but I highly doubt you have any voice/intruments that were above 3.6 unless you have some sweet gear.  Thats why you didnt see a difference.
<br />

<br />
Sorta like have 100 Str out of 255, then raising the cap to 305, and still only having 100 Str.
<br />

<br />
See here: <a target="_new" href="http://www.dotnetdiva.com/Forums/ShowPost.aspx?PostID=5572">http://www.dotnetdiva.com/Forums/ShowPost.aspx?PostID=5572</a></span></td>
